    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">Francesco Sforza to Miklós Oláh (Milan, 10 October 1534)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p>He was happy to read Oláh’s letter to Ghilino, at the end of which Oláh
                            added that he sends his regards. Oláh should write to him as frequently
                            as he can about everything, especially the English affairs. </p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Franciscus Sforciae dux Mediolani Nicolao Olao salutem. </p>
                <p>Reverende Amice Carissime! Quae de rebus publicis
                        <persName>Gilino</persName><note type="critic">Camillo Ghilino.</note>
                    secretario nostro scripsisti,<note type="critic">Ep.
                        479.</note><ref>/o:olahus.tei.15340413_2</ref> et libenter legimus et nobis
                    grata fuerunt, verum longe gratissima, quae in calce epistolae tuae adiunxisti,
                    salutem scilicet et sinceram voluntatem tuam, quam in rebus nostris omnibus
                    obtulisti. Fac tibi persuadeas, Olahe, pro huius tuae erga nos benevolentiae
                    hostimento, nos ad omnia, quae tua vel amicorum tuorum interesse intelligemus,
                    semper paratos fore. Interea ad nos quam saepissime de omnibus rebus et
                    praesertim Anglicis diligenter perscribas. In hoc certe nobis rem ex sententia
                    facturus. Vale et nos, ut facis, ama. </p>
                <p><placeName>Mediolani</placeName> VI. Idus Octobris 1534. </p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
